# Dependencies
node_modules/

# GitHub Actions workflows are intentionally not tracked here: the automation
# account used for commits lacks the GitHub `workflows` permission, so it cannot
# push .github/workflows/*. The files exist locally (and inside breeze.zip); add
# them to the repo from an account that has `workflows` permission. The intended
# ci.yml runs: npm ci -> syntax check -> npm test -> validate.sh -> build+upload
# breeze.zip. To track them, remove this rule or `git add -f`.
.github/workflows/

